<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-04T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="621" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d621">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W./6–445: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-04T13:00:00+03:00">June 4,
                                    1945—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1883. Personal for the Secretary. Hopkins<note n="49" xml:id="d621fn49">Harry L. Hopkins engaged in a series of conversations with Marshal
                                Stalin on May 26–June 6; he had retired from Government service
                                about May 12.</note> has cabled the President<note n="50" xml:id="d621fn50">Not found in Department files; but see memorandum
                                of conversation of June 14, <ref target="#pg_901">p.
                                901</ref>.</note> the results of our talks regarding Soviet activity
                            in the Far East (Reurtel 1200, June 2, 3 p.m.). As a result we have no
                            intention, unless instructed otherwise, to go further at this time or to
                            discuss any other subjects in the Dept’s memorandum referred to.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>